text: Rena is an unincorporated community in Clallam County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Rena was established in 1891, and remained in operation until 1902. The community was named after Reena Hooker. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Clallam County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Rena, Washington
